  <exercise>
    <title>Possible paired randomized differences</title>
    <statement>
      <p>Two observations were collected on each of five people. Which of the following could be a possible randomization of the paired differences given in the table below? If the set of values could not be a randomized set of differences, indicate why not.</p>
      
      <table xml:id="tbl-ex21-14">
        <title>Paired observations</title>
        <tabular halign="center">
          <row header="yes" bottom="medium">
            <cell></cell>
            <cell>1</cell>
            <cell>2</cell>
            <cell>3</cell>
            <cell>4</cell>
            <cell>5</cell>
          </row>
          <row>
            <cell>Observation 1</cell>
            <cell>3</cell>
            <cell>14</cell>
            <cell>4</cell>
            <cell>5</cell>
